<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="1" CELLSPACING="0" ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
	<TD  BGCOLOR="#660000">
	<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="3" CELLSPACING="1" WIDTH="100%">
	<TR BGCOLOR="#660000" ALIGN="LEFT">
		<TD WIDTH="20%"><FONT class="pn-title"><B>Author</B></FONT></TD>
		<TD><FONT class="pn-title"><b>Explicit's Point System</b></FONT></TD>
</TR>
	<TR BGCOLOR="#000000" ALIGN="LEFT">
<td ROWSPAN="3" valign="top"><font class="pn-normal"><a href="user.php?op=userinfo&amp;uname=Soullance"><b>Soullance</b></a></font><br><img src="images/avatar/012.gif" border="0" width="32" height="32""><BR><FONT class="pn-normal"><B>Guild Leader</B></font><br><img src="modules/phpBB_14/images/ranks/fivestars.gif" border="0" alt="Guild Leader"><br><font class="pn-normal">Posts: 357</font></td><TD valign="top"><img src="modules/phpBB_14/images/posticon.gif"><FONT class="pn-normal"><a name="2095">Posted: Sep 27, 2002 - 06:19 AM</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp</font></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><TD><FONT class="pn-normalLarge">GKP Mobs to Date: CT(PoF) / Grieg / AoW / King Tormax / Statue of Rallos Zek /Tunare / Lord Seru / Lord Yelinak / AL / HP / Creator / Blood / Emperor / Glyph / Cursed / Exiled / Rhag2 / Burrower(worm) / THO / Dain / Ntov / All VT mobs / Most PoP mobs<br />
<br />
Non GKP Mobs: Slime Ring / Servitor of Luclin / Rhag 1 / Umbral Mobs / WW Dragons / ST(to be reviewed) / Vindicator / All West Wing Tov Dragons / All others not listed here. <br />
<br />
<br />
What is GKP and Non-GKP mobs? <br />
- Mobs that drops items that no guild member buys are NoN GKP mobs. <br />
- Mobs that require less than 18people to kill. <br />
<br />
<br />
What is GKP? <br />
<br />
GKP is known as God Killing Points. Every time a player helps to kill one of those big creatures, they get God Killing Points, or GKP. <br />
(Points are controlled very tightly, None for use to express &quot;happy mood&quot; periods.) <br />
<br />
<br />
How is GKP derived from each mob? <br />
<br />
The amount of GKP you will get from a mob will be calculated from the total items value bought by players divided by the number of members present for that kill (PIPO - Points in = Point out).<br />
For example, if 40ppl killed CT in fear and 1x brain and 2x halo dropped. Brain cost 20pts, Halo cost 8pts. <br />
Brain and 1st Halo is bought by guildies. Other Halo rots. So total GKP per person will be calculated from 28pt divided by 40ppl, which will be 0.7pts per person. BUT if CT drops 3xhalos and only 1 is bought, then GKP per person will be 8pts divided by 40 = 0.2 <br />
<br />
<br />
What happens when I buy an item from a GKP mob? <br />
<br />
If a player wins an item, they lose GKP's equal to the value of the item. <br />
<br />
<br />
What if I won an item from a non-GKP mob? <br />
<br />
Nothing will be charged. Non-GKP mob does not utilize the GKP chart. <br />
<br />
<br />
How do we win a loot item? <br />
<br />
Everytime an item drops from a GKP mob, the loot leader will be calling loot values out in guild chat/raid chat. The loot leader(s) will take bids on each item via tells. The winner will be the bided person with the highest balance GKP spendable. <br />
&lt;Please also take note that the BOT system implimented on 9th Sept 2002 do effect GKP earnings.&gt; <br />
<br />
How do we distribute the non-GKP mob loots? <br />
<br />
- If item is for main characters, the loot will be either rolled OR winner picked by the person-in-charge. <br />
- Some items are allowed to be rolled by main characters for their twinks depending on situations. <br />
<br />
<br />
What if I want to get items for my twink? <br />
<br />
As we all know, we want each and everyone of us to be uba decked with gear to improve ourselves, therefore twinking is not encouraged. But you can still purchase items for your twinks. To be fair to everyone buying the same loots, GKP will be used for twink purchases. But it will vary in situations, such as, saving it for other main characters not online etc. <br />
<br />
<br />
Loot Limit! <br />
<br />
- Every character will have a loot purchase limited to 10 items ONLY per month (includes twink loots). Will subject to change if Items are not required by others or are going to rot. <br />
- No matter how many points you are leading with against another bidder, you can never buy more than 1 loot per dead mob.  You can buy as many loots as u can per day, but not more than 1 per mob.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
GKP updates <br />
<br />
Earned GKP will be updated in &quot;Points System List&quot; at the end of each day. Please take note of your point updates, check them daily if possible. <br />
Points updated cannot be changed after 3 days, eventhough you can provide solid proof of your existance in those raid(s). <br />
<br />
<br />
Adjustments to GKP Quarter Yearly <br />
<br />
GKP might get too high/ low as an average, for example: more than half of the total guild members have negative points, OR too many point leaders. Therefore, GKP will/might be adjusted as deem fit on a quarterly basis (March, June, Sept, and Dec). Adjustment actions such as reducing all player points by 20 OR adding all player points by 10. All adjustments will be carefully planned and posted one week before the actual event takes place. And all adjustments will be fair with everyone being treated equally. <br />
<br />
<br />
Buying Restrictions – Can I bid? <br />
<br />
- Main characters that can use the item will be considered top priority on GKP loots. <br />
- Items which main characters do not need will be announced in some situations open for twink purchases. <br />
<br />
<br />
Won Items <br />
<br />
Items won cannot be traded, sold or given away without prior consent. Items won from a GKP system can be given to a twink if an upgrade on that slot is known. All GKP items won for your main char and are found to be on twinks without any known upgrading on that particular slots will be severly dealt with. You can resell an item back to a guild member and get back full value as stated in &quot;item value link&quot; at that time transaction is made (not the value of item when u bought it). <br />
<br />
<br />
How and when are we going to start GKP? <br />
<br />
We started. We all got +50pts to start so as to reduce too many going negative pts from the beginning, and allowing newer members to be able to purchase items to get geared up and perform better. This 50pts will stay with everyone as long as they are in guild. This 50pts will be rotating around guildies as pts spendable. It may be adjusted as stated above under &quot;Adjustments to GKP Quarter Yearly&quot;. <br />
<br />
Negative GKP <br />
<br />
When you get negative in GKP points you are not elligible to purchase anything UNLESS the item is going to r0t due to no one needs, then you will get to loot and go more negative. BUT whenever your pts are lower than negative 20, you can never get another item even when it's going to r0t. (This will be adjusted accordingly in furture) <br />
<br />
Newly Implimented BOT System? <br />
<br />
This system is implimented to reward people who put in the effort to clear certain zones, such as PoG, also to those who are present and showed effort in failed attempts on certain mobs, and successful guild 1st kills. <br />
<br />
This is how the system works: <br />
<br />
- In every failed attempt (failed in killing a certain mob) 0.1 points will be awarded. <br />
- In every clearing of a zone (must be present at least 3/5 of the logs I take randomly during the clearing) 0.1 points will be awarded per 2 hourly. <br />
- In every &quot;guild first&quot; kills, points equal to the items purchased from the mob will be rewarded. <br />
<br />
<br />
For example, 30ppl are present at AL raid and there were 5 failed attempts, which will mean each person will be rewarded with 0.1x5 = 0.5 <br />
Successfully raids will be unchanged and points works as per normal under point system rules. <br />
<br />
As u know, our guild practises points in = points out system. We cannot reward anyone with eccessive points outside of this system, or the system will fail and eventually end up with large point hoggers in guild, which will discourage some members to play. <br />
This is when the BOT comes in. <br />
<br />
From the example above 30ppl in 5 failed attempts will be equal to 15pts spent by zzBOTzz (you'll notice zzBOTzz if u click the Points page on your left column). So, BOT loses 15pts on that day and the 30ppl present there will gain 0.5 each. <br />
But to stick to the PIPO (pt in=pt out) system we are practicing, points BOT spent will be given back to him weekly. So you will notice that, if BOT only spent 15pts that week, on Monday 15pts will be returned to BOT equally amongst EVERY guildmember (meaning 15 divide by the total number of guildmembers=amt each member will have to return to BOT). <br />
That will also mean that people who aren't on at all will have some slight adjustments in their points due to BOT getting points back from EVERYONE. <br />
<br />
And for &quot;Guild 1st&quot; kills this is how it works : <br />
<br />
- Guild 1st kills meaning mobs that haven't been killed by guild before will be updated with an actual loot purchase plus BOT pts equal to that purchase. So if 1st kill for example, Shei has 12pt loot purchased and divided amongst the 40 in raid(0.3each), 12pts will also be given by BOT to be divided amongst the 40 too(0.3each). <br />
BOT system works as per normal, points given out to members present at raid during that time, will be taken back by BOT at the end of each week from everyone in guild. <br />
To summarize what I said above, Guild 1st kills give you normal pts PLUS BOT pts equal to the normal pts. But BOT pts will be taken back, just the same as how BOT system works usually, only difference is the points value in this case is the same as loots purchased instead of 0.1. <br />
<br />
<br />
I can assure you that this system will not make a huge impact to your point differences if you play as per normally required. PST/GMT+8or9 peeps, will not get affected much by this system if you are to play as you usually do. <br />
<br />
I have done a survey on this system with my spreadsheets for the past 3weeks and noticed, Aussies, PST, Taiwanese, Japanese, etc members play as much or even more than some EST members. Therefore, time difference is not a good excuse. <br />
<br />
If everyone is on in every raid, there will be ZERO points changes every week. <br />
<br />
********new members start with 50pts too*********<br />
<br />
